HEADWORD: Insalutary
<hw>In*sal"u*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insaluteris</ets> : cf. F. <ets>insalutaire</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Salutary</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not salutary or
wholesome; unfavorable to health.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not tending to safety; productive of evil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insanability</ent>⟦br⟧
